Compliance With Recall Notices_40 CFR Part 51.370 




The federal regulation requires the states to establish methods to ensure that vehicles that are subject to enhanced
I/M and are included in an emission related recall receive the required repairs prior to completing the emission test
and/or renewing the vehicle registration. 


Act 166 and the Commonwealth's I/M regulation provide the legal authority to require owners to comply with emission
related recalls before completing the emission test and renewing the vehicle registration. The SIP includes procedures
