On-Road Testing_40 CFR Part 51.371 




On-road testing is required in enhanced I/M areas. The use of either remote sensing devices (RSD) or roadside pullovers
including tailpipe emission testing can be used to meet the federal regulations. The program must include on-road
testing of 0.5% of the subject fleet or 20,000 vehicles, whichever is less, in the nonattainment area or the I/M program
area. Motorists that have passed an emission test and are found to be high emitters as a result of an on-road test shall
be required to pass an out-of-cycle test. 


